```

## Troubleshooting

`repo discover` says `gh` is missing or unauthenticated:

```bash
gh auth login
gh auth status
```

`onboard` says the repo has no local path:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness repo set-path api-service ../api-service
```

This can happen when cloning was skipped because the destination already existed.

`cache refresh` says the repo must be approved or verified:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness approve api-service --all
```

`export` says the cache is stale:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness cache refresh api-service
```

`onboard` refuses to overwrite protected artifacts:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness improve api-service
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals list
```

That is expected. Once a pack is approved, accepted artifacts change through proposals, not direct regeneration.

 succeeded in 0ms:
/Users/alexmetelli/source/orgs-ai-harness

If a registered repo moves locally:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness repo set-path api-service ../new-api-service-path
```

Temporarily deactivate a repo:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness repo deactivate api-service \
  --reason "Paused until ownership changes are complete"
```

Remove a mistaken registration without deleting repo contents:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness repo remove api-service \
  --reason "Registered the wrong repository"
```

If a repo already has onboarding metadata, removal requires explicit force:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness repo remove api-service \
  --reason "Retired service" \
  --force
```

## Onboard A Repository

Start with a read-only scan if you want to inspect what the harness learned before generating skills:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness onboard api-service --scan-only
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness validate api-service
```

Scan-only writes:

```text
org-agent-skills/repos/api-service/
  onboarding-summary.md
  unknowns.yml
  scan/
    scan-manifest.yml
    hypothesis-map.yml
```

Sensitive files such as `.env`, private keys, token files, credentials, and local override files are skipped. Their paths may be recorded as metadata, but contents are not copied into generated artifacts.

Generate a draft skill pack:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness onboard api-service --llm codex --skill-target codex
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness validate api-service
```

Claude Code can be used instead:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness onboard api-service --llm claude --skill-target claude
```

Generate for both runtimes:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness onboard api-service --llm codex --skill-target both
```

Draft onboarding scans the repo, writes an LLM prompt to `llm-skill-generation-prompt.md`, invokes the selected LLM, validates generated skills from `llm-output/`, installs repo-specific skills into the selected runtime directories inside the cloned repo, snapshots those generated skills into the harness pack for review, and writes resolvers, evals, scripts, unknowns, and a pack report:

```text
org-agent-skills/repos/api-service/
  llm-output/
  skills/
  resolvers.yml
  evals/onboarding.yml
  scripts/
  pack-report.md
```

The full LLM transcript is written to `org-agent-skills/repos/<repo-id>/llm-skill-generation.log`. While generation is running, the CLI prints concise progress and a periodic `still running` line with the log path. After each repo, setup lists the generated skill names and the exact install directories used.

At this point the pack is still `draft`. It is not trusted until reviewed and approved.

## Review And Approve

Render a review view:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness approve api-service
```

The review shows generated artifacts, command permissions, risk notes, unresolved unknowns, and prior approved diff information when available.

Approve everything:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness approve api-service --all \
  --rationale "Initial reviewed onboarding pack"
```

Approve while excluding an artifact:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness approve api-service \
  --exclude repos/api-service/skills/build-test-debug/SKILL.md \
  --rationale "Use existing manual test guidance for now"
```

Reject a draft pack:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness reject api-service \
  --reason "Generated guidance is too uncertain"
```

Approved packs become `approved-unverified`. Approved artifacts are protected. Later generation cannot overwrite them directly; changes go through proposals.

## Run Eval Replay

Run local eval replay against an approved pack:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness eval api-service
```

The report includes baseline pass rate, skill-pack pass rate, improvement delta, rediscovery cost delta, blocking unknowns, command approvals used, and final status.

Common outcomes:

- `verified`: approved pack met verification thresholds.
- `approved-unverified`: approved pack did not meet verification thresholds, but no blocking failure forced investigation.
- `needs-investigation`: blocking unknowns or safety failures remain.

Run a non-verifying development replay:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness eval api-service --development
```

Use development replay when you want reports and traces without changing repo verification status.

## Publish Skills To A Code Repo

Refresh the repo-local pinned cache:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness cache refresh api-service
```

This writes into the selected code repo:

```text
api-service/
  .agent-harness.yml
  .agent-harness/
    cache/
      pack-ref
      metadata.json
      org/
      repos/api-service/
      exports/
```

Export for a runtime:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness export generic api-service
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness export codex api-service
```

Exports are written under:

```text
api-service/.agent-harness/cache/exports/<target>/
```

Supported targets:

- `generic`
- `codex`

Draft packs do not export by default. Development-only export flags exist for intentional local testing:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness export generic api-service --allow-draft
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness export generic api-service --development
```

## Inspect Repo State

Use explain when you need to understand what the harness currently believes:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness explain api-service
```

Explain output includes coverage, lifecycle status, pack ref, cache status, approved skills, triggers, evals, pass rates, unresolved unknowns, boundary decisions, and recent proposals.

## Improve From Traces

After evals, command approvals, or approval comments exist, ask the harness to propose improvements:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness improve api-service
```

If there is enough evidence, it creates:

```text
org-agent-skills/proposals/prop_001/
  summary.md
  evidence.jsonl
  patch.diff
  metadata.yml
```

Review proposals:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals list
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals show prop_001
```

Apply a proposal:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals apply prop_001 --yes
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness validate api-service
```

Reject a proposal:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals reject prop_001 \
  --reason "Insufficient evidence"
```

Proposal evidence is redacted. Sensitive skipped file contents are not copied into proposal evidence.

After applying a proposal, refresh the cache before exporting:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness cache refresh api-service
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness export codex api-service
```

Exports intentionally fail as stale if an applied proposal is not yet included in the cache.

## Refresh After Source Changes

When a repository has changed since onboarding, create refresh proposals:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness refresh api-service
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals list
```

Refresh detects the current source commit against the last recorded onboarding source commit. It creates proposals only. It does not overwrite accepted skills, summaries, resolvers, evals, or scripts.

Review and apply refresh proposals the same way:

```bash
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals show prop_002
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness proposals apply prop_002 --yes
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness validate api-service
python3 -m orgs_ai_harness cache refresh api-service
```

