# Sprint 07: Local Eval Replay and Verification

## Goal

Run approved onboarding evals locally with and without the approved skill pack, score the results, and determine whether the pack is `verified` or remains `approved-unverified`.

## Complete Working Functionality

A user can run `harness eval <repo-id>` and receive a report containing baseline pass rate, skill-pack pass rate, improvement delta, rediscovery cost delta, and final pack status.

## User Outcome

The QA or platform owner can decide whether the generated skill pack measurably improves repo understanding instead of trusting generated documentation by default.

## Delivery Rule

Do not implement this sprint as horizontal phases such as adapter interface, scoring functions, trace schema, report writer, and tests. Each issue must be a vertical slice that proves one user-visible or test-visible eval behavior from CLI command through approved pack/eval checks, adapter execution, scoring, local traces, report output, and verification status where needed.

